OL,3,CUtility bills and tax hikes drive
OL,4,Cinflation higher
OL,6,FRetailers say those costs have now
OL,7,Fbeen passed on to consumers - and
OL,8,Fthey're reminding the government that
OL,9,Fthey warned this would happen.
OL,11,FThe Bank of England predicted the
OL,12,FBudget would push up inflation. It's
OL,13,Fpossible, though not yet certain, that
OL,14,Ffirms have responded by raising prices
OL,15,Fmore aggressively than the Bank
OL,16,Fassumed.
